==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*κακός / kakos / kak-os'
*Apparently a primary word; worthless (intrinsically such; whereas G4190 properly refers to effects), that is, (subjectively) depraved, or (objectively) injurious: 

===Adjective===
'''κακός'''

# [[bad]], [[evil]], [[harm]], [[ill]], noisome, [[wicked]].

